President Trump and First Lady Melania Trump visited Mt. Rushmore in South Dakota to celebrate Independence Day. In his remarks, the President thanked various individuals and groups, including the South Dakota Army and Air National Guard and the U.S. Air Force. He expressed gratitude to veterans, law enforcement, first responders, and healthcare workers. The President also spoke about the current climate of protests and statue removals, calling it a "merciless campaign" to erase American history and values. He condemned what he referred to as "cancel culture" and the "radical ideology" that seeks to dismantle American heritage. The President announced the creation of the National Garden of American Heroes, a park that will feature statues of prominent Americans. He concluded his remarks by expressing his love for the country and his belief in American greatness.